  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What marks are required in the IISER aptitude test in order to get admission in any of the IISERs? Also, what rank in the JEE (Advanced) is good enough?",
  "response": "Admission to the **Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs)** can be secured through multiple channels, including the **IISER Aptitude Test (IAT)**, **JEE (Advanced)**, and **Kishore Vaigyanik Protsahan Yojana (KVPY)**. The eligibility and cutoff marks or ranks vary each year based on factors like the number of applicants, difficulty level of the exam, and available seats. Here\u2019s a general overview:\n\n---\n\n### **1. IISER Aptitude Test (IAT) Marks**\n- **Eligibility**: You need to score above the **IISER cutoff** in the IAT to secure admission. The cutoff varies annually.\n- **Past Trends** (Approximate):\n  - General category: 50-60% or higher in the IAT.\n  - Reserved categories: Lower threshold, depending on the category.\n- **Focus**: While there is no fixed mark, aim to score as high as possible, especially in the General Aptitude, Mathematics, and Science sections.\n\n---\n\n### **2. JEE (Advanced) Rank**\n- **Eligibility**: If applying through JEE (Advanced), you need to have a valid rank.\n- **Good Rank**: Typically, a rank **below 10,000** (General category) is considered competitive for IISER admission.\n- **Reserved Categories**: Ranks can be significantly higher (e.g., SC/ST/OBC candidates with ranks around 20,000 to 30,000 may also secure admission).\n\n---\n\n### **3. KVPY Fellowship**\n- **Eligibility**: If you hold a KVPY fellowship, you are directly eligible for IISER admission, provided you meet the fellowship criteria.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Points to Note**\n- **Seats Availability**: IISERs have a limited number of seats (~1,500 across all IISERs), so competition is high.\n- **Weightage**: For IAT, the final score is calculated based on the Aptitude Test (85%) and Class XII board marks (15%).\n- **Cutoff Variations**: Cutoffs differ across IISERs and categories.\n\n---\n\n### **Recommendation**\n- For IAT: Aim to score **60% or higher** to maximize your chances.\n- For JEE (Advanced): A rank **below 10,000** is generally safe (though lower ranks improve your odds).\n- For KVPY: Securing the fellowship itself ensures eligibility.\n\nAlways check the official IISER admission portal for the latest cutoffs and updates.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
